#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Several of the data fields are held in an internal format which may not be "
"immediately useful to external programs. In these cases, the information has "
"been duplicated in both internal and external formats."
msgstr ""
"Nekoliko polja podataka se drži u internom formatu koji možda neće biti "
"koristan eksternim programima već u samom početku. U ovim slučajevima, "
"informacija je duplicirana i u interne i u eksterne formate."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:444
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Monetary amounts and share values are shown both in numerator/denominator "
#| "format, and, with a field name suffixed with 'Formatted', in the form as "
#| "shown on your screens."
msgid ""
"Monetary amounts and share values are shown both in numerator/denominator "
"format, and, with a field name suffixed with <quote> <literal>Formatted</"
"literal> </quote>, in the form as typically displayed."
msgstr ""
"Monetarne vrijednosti i vrijednosti dionica su prikazane u brojnik/nazivnik "
"formatu i ukoliko polje ima sufiks 'Formatted' onda su prikazani u formi "
"koja se nalazi na vašim ekranima."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:450
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Similarly, some fields, such as account type appear both as a numeric "
#| "code, and in a field suffixed 'String' in the form and language of the "
#| "application."
msgid ""
"Similarly, some fields, such as account type appear both as a numeric code, "
"and in a field suffixed '<literal>String</literal>' in the form and language "
"of the application."
msgstr ""
"Slično, neka polja kao što je polje za račun su prikazani i kao numerički "
"kod i kao polje sa sufiksom 'String' u formi i jeziku aplikacije."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Updating your data"
msgstr "Ažururanje podataka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:458
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Having data in an industry standard format does give you the ability to "
#| "modify it outside the &kappname; application. DO NOT DO IT unless you "
#| "really know what you are doing, and always be certain to make a backup "
#| "copy of your data first. If you get it wrong, &kappname; may not be able "
#| "to access your data, and you could even end up losing it altogether. You "
#| "have been warned!"
msgid ""
"Having data in an industry standard format does give you the ability to "
"modify it outside the &kmymoney; application. DO NOT DO IT unless you really "
"know what you are doing, and always be certain to make a backup copy of your "
"data first. If you get it wrong, &kmymoney; may not be able to access your "
"data, and you could even end up losing it altogether. You have been warned!"
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko podatke držite u industrijskom standardnom formatu, imacete "
"mogucnost da ih modificirate izvan &kappname; aplikacije. NEMOJTE TO RADITI "
"osim ako stvarno znate šta radite i uvijek napravite backup kopiju podataka "
"sa kojim radite. Ukoliko pogriješite, &kappname; neće moći pristupiti vašim "
"podacima i možda ćete ih na kraju i izgubiti skroz. Upozoreni ste!"

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:467
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stored queries"
msgstr "Pohranjeni upiti"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:468
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Most database systems allow you to store commonly used queries and "
#| "procedures, and in some cases, these may be held as tables or other "
#| "objects within your database itself. As you will have guessed from the "
#| "above, all the tables used by &kappname; begin with the lowercase letters "
#| "'kmm'. This standard will be maintained, and only tables beginning with "
#| "these letters will be updated. Thus, provided you avoid these in the "
#| "naming of your queries &etc;, you should not experience any problems."
msgid ""
"Most database systems allow you to store commonly used queries and "
"procedures, and in some cases, these may be held as tables or other objects "
"within your database itself. As you will have guessed from the above, all "
"the tables used by &kmymoney; begin with the lowercase letters "
"'<literal>kmm</literal>'. This standard will be maintained, and only tables "
"beginning with these letters will be updated. Thus, provided you avoid these "
"in the naming of your queries &etc;, you should not experience any problems."
msgstr ""
"Većina sistema baza podataka vam omogućavaju da pohranite česte upite i "
"procedure, i u nekim slučajevima ih možete spasiti kao tabele ili neke druge "
"objekte unutar same baze podataka. Kao što možete pretpostaviti iz već "
"navedenog, sve tabele korištene od strane &kappname; počinju sa malim "
"slovima 'kmm'. Ovaj standard će biti održan i samo tabele čije ime počinje "
"ovim slovima će biti ažurirane. Ukoliko ih budete izbjegavali u imenovanju "
"upita &etc;, ne biste trebali naići na bilo kakve probleme."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:480
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manual database creation"
msgstr "Ručno kreiranje baze podataka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section covers more advanced database usage and may be skipped by the "
"general user."
msgstr ""
"Ovo poglavlje obuhvata naprednije korištenje baze podataka i može biti "
"preskočeno od strane uobičajenog korisnika."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "When to use"
msgstr "Kada koristiti"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:488
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "There may be occasions when &kappname; is unable to create the database "
#| "automatically, or creates it without some options required by the user. "
#| "For example, the database system used may not completely conform to "
#| "standard SQL usage, or support may be introduced for new systems which "
#| "have not been fully tested in &kappname;."
msgid ""
"There may be occasions when &kmymoney; is unable to create the database "
"automatically, or creates it without some options required by the user. For "
"example, the database system used may not completely conform to standard SQL "
"usage, or support may be introduced for new systems which have not been "
"fully tested in &kmymoney;."
msgstr ""
"Možda će biti situacija kada &kappname; neće biti u mogućnosti da kreira "
"bazu podataka automatski ili je kreira bez nekih opcija traženih od strane "
"korisnika. Npr. sistem baze podataka koji se koristi možda neće u potpunosti "
"odgovarati standardu SQL upotrebe ili se može inicirati podrška nekim novim "
"sistemima koji još nisu u potpunosti testirani u &kappname;."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:496
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Prior to using this facility, you should try just creating the database "
#| "entry itself (&ie; with the CREATE DATABASE statement). Provided the "
#| "database exists, &kappname; may well be able to create the tables, &etc; "
#| "in the normal database save procedure described above."
msgid ""
"Prior to using this facility, you should try just creating the database "
"entry itself (&ie; with the <literal>CREATE DATABASE</literal> statement). "
"Provided the database exists, &kmymoney; may well be able to create the "
"tables, &etc; in the normal database save procedure described above."
msgstr ""
"Prije korištenja ove mogućnosti, trebali biste prvo probati samo kreirati "
"unos baze podataka(&ie; sa CREATE DATABASE). Ukoliko baza podataka postoji, "
"&kappname; će vjerovatno napraviti tabele, &etc; u sigurnoj proceduri baze "
"podataka opisanoj iznad."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating the SQL"
msgstr "Generiranje SQL-a"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:505
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If this fails, it is possible to generate the basic SQL commands needed "
#| "to create the various tables, views and indexes required by the "
#| "application. Select <guimenuitem>Generate Database SQL</guimenuitem> from "
#| "the <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> menu. This will present the following dialog:"
msgid ""
"If this fails, it is possible to generate the basic SQL commands needed to "
"create the various tables, views, and indexes required by the application. "
"Select the <menuchoice> <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Generate "
"Database SQL</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> menu item. This will present the "
"following dialog:"
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko ovo podbaci, moguće je generirati osnovne SQL komande potrebne za "
"kreiranje raznih tabela, pregleda i indeksa zahtijevanih od strane "
"aplikacije. Odaberite <guimenuitem>Generate Database SQL</guimenuitem> iz "
"<guimenu>Tools</guimenu> menija. Ovo će prikazati sljedeći dijalog:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: details-database.docbook:513
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>generate sql to create a database</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: details-database.docbook:519
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>generate sql to create a database</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On selecting the database type, the appropriate SQL will appear in the "
"<guilabel>SQL for creation</guilabel> text box; this can be edited by the "
"user, or saved to a text file by clicking <guibutton>Save SQL</guibutton>. "
"In the latter case, the database must be created using the administrative "
"functions provided by the database system."
msgstr ""
"Prilikom odabira tipa baze podataka, odgovarajući SQL će se pojaviti u "
"<guilabel>SQL for creation</guilabel> tekst polju; ovo može biti uređeno od "
"strane korisnika ili spašeno kao tekst datoteka klikom na <guibutton>Save "
"SQL</guibutton>. U ovom zadnjem slučaju, baza podataka mora biti kreirana "
"upotrebom administrativnih funkcija obezbijeđenih od strane sistema baze "
"podataka."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:532
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If after editing the text in the dialog, you want &kappname; to create "
#| "the database, you will need to complete the other fields in the dialog, "
#| "as detailed in <link linkend=\"details.database.selectdatabase\">Creating "
#| "a Database</link> above, and click <guibutton>Create Tables</guibutton>. "
#| "Note that, except in the case of SQLite, you will need either to include "
#| "a suitable CREATE DATABASE statement as the first command, or have "
#| "previously issued such a command externally to &kappname;"
msgid ""
"If after editing the text in the dialog, you want &kmymoney; to create the "
"database, you will need to complete the other fields in the dialog, as "
"detailed in <link linkend=\"details.database.selectdatabase\">Creating a "
"Database</link> above, and click <guibutton>Create Tables</guibutton>. Note "
"that, except in the case of SQLite, you will need either to include a "
"suitable <literal>CREATE DATABASE</literal> statement as the first command, "
"or have previously issued such a command externally to &kmymoney;."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko nakon uređivanja teksta u dijalogu želite da &kappname; kreira bazu "
"podataka, morate popuniti i ostala polja u dijalogu, kao što je opisano u "
"<link linkend=\"details.database.selectdatabase\">Kreiranje baze podataka</"
"link> iznad i potom kliknite na <guibutton>Kreiraj tabele</guibutton>. "
"Primijetite da osim u slučaju SQLite-a, morate uključiti ili odgovarajuću "
"CREATE DATABASE izjavu kao prvu komandu ili prethodno ovome izdati takvu "
"komandu &kappname; eksterno."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:543
#, no-c-format
msgid "Warning"
msgstr "Upozorenje"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:544
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You should be very careful editing the definitions of any of the basic "
#| "tables or views (those with names beginning with 'kmm'). Some changes, "
#| "such as increasing the length of an integer field, may have little "
#| "impact, but you should not remove or change the sequence of any fields, "
#| "or &kappname; may refuse to function, or may corrupt your data."
msgid ""
"You should be very careful editing the definitions of any of the basic "
"tables or views (those with names beginning with '<literal>kmm</literal>'.) "
"Some changes, such as increasing the length of an integer field, may have "
"little impact, but you should not remove or change the sequence of any "
"fields, or &kmymoney; may refuse to function, or may corrupt your data."
msgstr ""
"Morate biti vrlo oprezni prilikom uređivanja definicija bilo koje osnovne "
"tabele ili pregleda (onih cije ime pocinje sa 'kmm'). Neke promjene, kao što "
"je povečavanje polja cijelog broja mogu imati mali utjecaj, ali ne smije te "
"ukloniti ili promijeniti redoslijed polja. U suprotnom, &kappname; može "
"prestati sa radom ili ćak korumpirati vaše podatke."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:552
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Whilst adding or removing indexes may improve performance, you should "
#| "also be aware that the opposite may happen. Some knowledge of the "
#| "internal operation of &kappname; may help to get the best performance in "
#| "these circumstances."
msgid ""
"While adding or removing indexes may improve performance, you should also be "
"aware that the opposite may happen. Some knowledge of the internal operation "
"of &kmymoney; may help to get the best performance in these circumstances."
msgstr ""
"Dok dodavanje i uklanjanje indeksa može poboljšati performanse, morate znati "
"da se i suprotno može dogoditi. Određeno poznavanje internih operacija "
"&kappname; vam može pomoći da dobijete najbolje performanse pri ovakvim "
"okolnostima."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:560
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encryption"
msgstr "Šifrovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encryption of data in your database is not currently supported."
msgstr ""
"Zaštitno kodiranje podataka u vašim bazama podataka trenutno nije podržano."

